						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Fragment of a stone in the compound of Śankaraliṅga temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Vīra-Tribhuvanamalla (Bijjala)—(Date Lost).</p>						

						<p>This inscription, the date of which is lost, refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Vīra-Tribhuvanamalla.</hi> It registers a gift of land by Bammarasa, the <hi rend="italic">prabhu</hi> of Goṇavalage, Ayicha, Kalleya-nāyaka and others and the <hi rend="italic">Eṇṭu-Hiṭṭus.</hi> Mentions <hi rend="bold">Tarddavāḍi-nāḍu.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
